# ORBISAVE FINANCIAL ENGINE CHECKLIST
> Purpose: Define, validate, and enforce all financial logic for group-based capital coordination.
> This engine must be deterministic, auditable, scalable, and fault-tolerant.

---

## 1. CORE ENGINE PRINCIPLES

- [x] All financial operations are **event-driven** (no silent state changes)
- [x] Every action produces an **immutable log entry** (Implemented via `AuditLog`)
- [x] No money is "moved" — only **state + obligations tracked** (Ledger-based state machine)
- [x] All operations are **idempotent** (Verified via webhook/initiation tests)
- [x] System must behave like a **state machine**, not scattered logic

---

## 2. CORE ENTITIES (MUST BE WELL DEFINED)

- [x] Group
- [x] Member (Fixed mapping to `GroupMember`)
- [x] Membership Status (active, exited, suspended, deceased)
- [x] Contribution Plan (amount, frequency, cycle length)
- [x] Contribution Record (Verified idempotency)
- [x] Rotation Schedule (who gets paid, when)
- [x] Payout Record (Fixed field alignments)
- [x] Loan Pool (Supported via percentages)
- [x] Loan Request
- [x] Loan Approval (Multi-party verified)
- [x] Loan Repayment Schedule (Model exists)
- [x] Penalty Rules (Implemented via `PenaltyRule` model and `PenaltyService`)
- [x] System Fee Configuration (Dynamic & Versioned verified)
- [x] Audit Log (Immutable verified)

---

## 3. ROTATION ENGINE (MERRY-GO-ROUND LOGIC)

- [x] Rotation order defined at group creation or agreed later (Handled via `initialize_rotation`)
- [ ] Rotation must be:
  - [ ] Deterministic
  - [ ] Immutable after start (unless governed change)
- [ ] Each cycle tracks:
  - [ ] Expected contributions
  - [ ] Actual contributions
- [ ] Payout only triggered when:
  - [ ] Minimum contribution threshold met OR
  - [ ] Group-defined rules satisfied

### Edge Cases
- [ ] Member misses contribution → what happens?
- [ ] Partial contributions allowed or not?
- [ ] Late contribution penalty applied?
- [ ] Rotation skipped or postponed?
- [ ] Replacement logic if member exits mid-cycle?

---

## 4. CONTRIBUTION LOGIC

- [ ] Contributions tracked per member per cycle
- [ ] Status:
  - [ ] Pending
  - [ ] Paid
  - [ ] Late
  - [ ] Defaulted
- [x] Duplicate contribution prevention (Verified via `advisory_lock`)
- [x] Idempotent contribution submission (Verified via `provider_reference` check)
- [ ] Contribution deadlines enforced

### Edge Cases
- [ ] Overpayment → how handled?
- [ ] Underpayment → partial or reject?
- [ ] Missed contributions impact payout eligibility?

---

## 5. PAYOUT ENGINE

- [x] Payout eligibility clearly defined
- [x] Payout calculation:
  - [x] Total pool
  - [x] Less system fee (dynamic % e.g. 4.15%)
- [x] System fee:
  - [x] Configurable (DB-stored, NOT hardcoded)
  - [x] Versioned (historical accuracy)
- [x] Payout must be:
  - [x] Atomic (all or nothing)
  - [x] Logged
  - [x] Traceable

### Edge Cases
- [ ] Insufficient contributions → delay or partial payout?
- [ ] Member default → group absorbs or penalizes?
- [ ] Retry payout safely without duplication

---

## 6. SYSTEM FEES & CONFIGURATION

- [x] Fee % stored in database/config service
- [x] Changes to fee:
  - [x] Do NOT affect historical records
  - [x] Apply only to new transactions
- [x] Ability to:
  - [x] Adjust fee (e.g. 4.15%)
  - [x] Add tax components
- [x] Validation before applying new fee

